entry.def: A commander is an officer in charge of a military operation or organization.

entry.def: A commander is an officer in the Royal Navy or the U.S. Navy.

means.word_mean: 1. an officer in command of a military unit
2. someone in an official position of authority who can command or control others
3. a commissioned naval officer who ranks above a lieutenant commander and below a captain
